1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Fiber Flightcheck
Know whether a Fiber payment can succeed before sending it.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:25,000
A running Fiber node can still fail at payment time.
Flightcheck checks node, channel, funding, asset, and liquidity state first.

3
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Start with a real request: can this node send 10 CKB now?

4
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:52,000
The app server queries its private FNN RPC.
The browser never receives or selects that endpoint.

5
00:00:52,000 --> 00:01:05,000
One result combines network health, synchronization, peers,
channels, asset support, and directional capacity.

6
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:20,000
ChannelReady confirms lifecycle state.
Sendable and receivable balances are evaluated separately.

7
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:35,000
On-chain CKB funding and off-chain channel liquidity answer
different operational questions, so Flightcheck reports both.

8
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Payment Proof runs a real server-side keysend dry run
against an operator-configured Fiber peer.

9
00:01:48,000 --> 00:02:05,000
The public proof is amount-capped, cooldown-limited, target-restricted,
and redacted. Live payment execution remains locked.

10
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Every check can produce auditable Markdown, JSON, or PDF evidence.

11
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:25,000
The same structured result is reusable from the UI, CLI, API, or CI.

12
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:38,000
Scenario Lab regression-tests known failure states
without disrupting the live Fiber node.

13
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Simulated scenarios are clearly separated from
the live readiness and payment-proof paths.

14
00:02:45,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Live Fiber state. One readiness decision. One next action.
github.com/Jayrodri088/fiber-flightcheck
